traceability.evidence:
In src/print-outdated.js the JSON branch emits only name, current, wanted, latest, age (null) for each package and summary fields, e.g.:

  const rows = entries.map(([name, info]) => [name, info.current, info.wanted, info.latest, null]);
  console.log(jsonFormatter({ rows, summary, thresholds, timestamp }));

The jsonFormatter then maps array rows to objects with properties {name, current, wanted, latest, age} only.  It does not include vulnerabilities, severity thresholds, recommended versions, package type, filtered flag or filterReason as required by the spec (see prompts/008.0-DEV-JSON-OUTPUT.md).
